  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "A collaborative New Year's greeting collage on paper (330 x 412 mm) made in late **1970** by **Niki de Saint-Phalle** (Neuilly-sur-Seine, 1930 – La Jolla, 2002) and **Jean Tinguely** (Fribourg, 1925 – Bern, 1991), sent for New Year **1971** to **Edy de Wilde** (then director of the Stedelijk Museum Amsterdam) and his partner **Nono Reinhold**. Executed in collage, felt-tip marker, ballpoint pen, and adhesive tape. The inscription thanks de Wilde for dinner and invites the recipients to visit the couple at **Soisy-sur-Ecole** — their studio/residence 44 km southeast of Paris, also the site of their ongoing work on the monumental sculpture **Le Cyclop** (begun 1969). Donated to Teylers in 1998 via the **Stichting Reinhold De Wilde**. Designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.",
